    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-17T03:41:29+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-17T03:41:29+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T18:11:29Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T18:11:29Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over the Tasman Sea extends a ridge over eastern parts of SA. A low pressure system south of the Bight will remain slow-moving until later Thursday when it will move southeastwards. An associated cold front will move across SA today followed by a second front later Thursday and Friday. A high pressure system will move across from the west over the weekend.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
